<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60d2/1a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Pearson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-29T17:00:00-05:00">January 29, 1927—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2. Instruction No. 81, August 16, 1923.<note n="1" xml:id="d115fn1">Not printed; it transmitted a draft treaty of friendship and
                                    commerce which had been submitted to the Finnish Government
                                    through its Legation in Washington. The draft was similar to
                                    that transmitted to the Ambassador in Spain, May 18, 1923, <ref target="frus1923v02#pg_831"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                                        p. 831</ref>.</note> Ascertain if negotiation of Treaty of
                                Friendship Commerce and Consular Rights can be expedited. Report
                                promptly.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>